{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019cTUA5MEX4QuoXnbtBr5VY","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * A module containing utilities which return thunks of data\n     3→ * @since 0.0.0\n     4→ * @module @beep/utils/thunk\n     5→ */\n     6→\n     7→import { Effect } from \"effect\";\n     8→import * as A from \"effect/Array\";\n     9→import * as R from \"effect/Record\";\n    10→\n    11→type LazyArg<A> = () => A;\n    12→\n    13→/**\n    14→ * Creates a thunk that always returns the provided value.\n    15→ *\n    16→ * @since 0.0.0\n    17→ */\n    18→export const thunk =\n    19→  <A>(value: A): LazyArg<A> =>\n    20→  () =>\n    21→    value;\n    22→\n    23→/**\n    24→ * Returns a thunk that always yields `null`.\n    25→ *\n    26→ * @since 0.0.0\n    27→ */\n    28→export const thunkNull = thunk(null);\n    29→\n    30→/**\n    31→ * Returns a thunk that always yields `undefined`.\n    32→ *\n    33→ * @since 0.0.0\n    34→ */\n    35→export const thunkUndefined = thunk(undefined);\n    36→\n    37→/**\n    38→ * Returns a thunk that always yields `void 0`.\n    39→ *\n    40→ * @since 0.0.0\n    41→ */\n    42→export const thunkVoid = thunk(void 0);\n    43→\n    44→/**\n    45→ * Returns a thunk that always yields `true`.\n    46→ *\n    47→ * @since 0.0.0\n    48→ */\n    49→export const thunkTrue = thunk(true);\n    50→\n    51→/**\n    52→ * Returns a thunk that always yields `false`.\n    53→ *\n    54→ * @since 0.0.0\n    55→ */\n    56→export const thunkFalse = thunk(false);\n    57→\n    58→/**\n    59→ * Returns a thunk that always yields the empty string.\n    60→ *\n    61→ * @since 0.0.0\n    62→ */\n    63→export const thunkEmptyStr = thunk(\"\");\n    64→\n    65→/**\n    66→ * Returns a thunk that always yields `0`.\n    67→ *\n    68→ * @since 0.0.0\n    69→ */\n    70→export const thunk0 = thunk(0);\n    71→\n    72→/**\n    73→ * Returns a thunk that always yields `0`.\n    74→ *\n    75→ * @since 0.0.0\n    76→ */\n    77→export const thunk1 = thunk(0);\n    78→\n    79→/**\n    80→ * Returns a thunk that yields a fresh empty mutable array.\n    81→ *\n    82→ * @since 0.0.0\n    83→ */\n    84→export const thunkEmptyArray = <A = never>(): LazyArg<Array<A>> => A.empty<A>;\n    85→\n    86→/**\n    87→ * Returns a thunk that yields a fresh empty readonly array.\n    88→ *\n    89→ * @since 0.0.0\n    90→ */\n    91→export const thunkEmptyReadonlyArray = <A = never>(): LazyArg<ReadonlyArray<A>> => A.empty<A>;\n    92→\n    93→/**\n    94→ * Lifts an Effect value into a thunk.\n    95→ *\n    96→ * @since 0.0.0\n    97→ */\n    98→export const thunkEffect = <A, E, R>(effect: Effect.Effect<A, E, R>): LazyArg<Effect.Effect<A, E, R>> => thunk(effect);\n    99→\n   100→/**\n   101→ * Returns a thunk for `Effect.void`.\n   102→ *\n   103→ * @since 0.0.0\n   104→ */\n   105→export const thunkEffectVoid = thunkEffect(Effect.void);\n   106→\n   107→/**\n   108→ * Returns a thunk for `Effect.succeed(a)`.\n   109→ *\n   110→ * @since 0.0.0\n   111→ */\n   112→export const thunkEffectSucceed = <A>(a: A): LazyArg<Effect.Effect<unknown, never, A>> =>\n   113→  thunkEffect(Effect.succeed(a));\n   114→\n   115→/**\n   116→ * Returns a thunk that yields an empty record.\n   117→ *\n   118→ * @since 0.0.0\n   119→ */\n   120→export const thunkEmptyRecord = <K extends string | symbol = never, V = never>() => R.empty<K, V>();\n   121→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01FoP91GGXZmiSCzHSJ42Lfo","session_id":"ed826b28-f569-4d3f-95d3-b6409c9f2336","uuid":"5620508e-7332-4847-9287-1d8c772978c6"}
