export class LiteralNotInSetError extends S.TaggedErrorClass<LiteralNotInSetError>($I`LiteralNotInSetError`)(\n  \"LiteralNotInSetError\",\n  {\n    literals: S.Array(LiteralValueSchema),\n    input: S.Array(LiteralValueSchema),\n  },\n  $I.annote(\"LiteralNotInSetError\", {\n    title: \"Not In Literals Error\",\n    description: \"Error thrown when an input value is not found in the provided literals array.\",\n  })\n) {}\n```\n\n#### Error Handling Patterns:\n\n1. **Schema-based Error Classes**: All errors extend `S.TaggedErrorClass` from Effect/Schema\n   - Provides structured error typing\n   - Integrates with schema serialization\n   - Uses identity system for error identification\n\n2. **Error Channel Pattern** (via Effect):\n   - Errors wrapped in schema validation context\n   - Uses `S.decodeUnknownSync()` and related decode functions\n   - Exceptions thrown synchronously for validation failures\n\n3. **Schema Validation Errors**:\n   - Schema issues use `SchemaIssue` types from Effect\n   - Formatted via `SchemaIssue.makeFormatterStandardSchemaV1(options)(err.issue)`\n   - Custom hooks for leaf and check issues via i18n\n\n---\n\n### 3. HOW SCHEMA IS USED\n\n#### Schema Integration Pattern:\n\n```typescript\n// From @beep/identity/Id.ts\nconst SegmentSchema = S.String.check(SegmentCheck);\nconst ModuleSegmentSchema = SegmentSchema.check(ModuleSegmentCheck);\nconst BaseSegmentSchema = S.String.check(...);\n\n// Decode utilities created from schemas\nconst decodeString = S.decodeUnknownSync(S.String);\nconst decodeSegment = S.decodeUnknownSync(SegmentSchema);\nconst decodeModuleSegment = S.decodeUnknownSync(ModuleSegmentSchema);\nconst decodeBaseSegment = S.decodeUnknownSync(BaseSegmentSchema);\n```\n\n#### Schema Annotations with Identity:\n\n```typescript\n// From @beep/schema/ArrayOf.ts\nconst $I = $SchemaId.create(\"ArrayOf\");\nexport const ArrayOfStrings = S.Array(S.String).annotate(\n  $I.annote(\"ArrayOfStrings\", {\n    description: \"An array of strings\",\n  })\n);\n```\n\n#### Error Schema Definition:\n\n```typescript\n// From @beep/schema/LiteralKit.ts\nconst LiteralValueSchema = S.Union([S.String, S.BigInt, S.Boolean, S.Number]);\n\nexport class LiteralNotInSetError extends S.TaggedErrorClass<LiteralNotInSetError>($I`LiteralNotInSetError`)(\n  \"LiteralNotInSetError\",\n  {\n    literals: S.Array(LiteralValueSchema),\n    input: S.Array(LiteralValueSchema),\n  },\n  // ... annotations\n) {}\n```\n\n#### Schema Usage in Messages:\n\n```typescript\n// From @beep/messages/i18n.ts\nexport function getLogIssues(options?: GetLogIssuesOptions) {\n  return <S extends S.Codec<unknown, unknown>>(schema: S, input: unknown) => {\n    S.decodeUnknownExit(schema)(input, { errors: \"all\" }).pipe(\n      Exit.mapError((err) => SchemaIssue.makeFormatterStandardSchemaV1(options)(err.issue).issues)\n    )\n  };\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. HOW EFFECT IS USED\n\n#### Effect Imports and Patterns:\n\n**Core Effect Utilities:**\n```typescript\n// From Struct.ts\nimport { Function as F, String as Str } from \"effect\";\nimport * as O from \"effect/Option\";\nimport * as P from \"effect/Predicate\";\n\n// From thunk.ts\nimport { Effect } from \"effect\";\nimport * as A from \"effect/Array\";\nimport * as R from \"effect/Record\";\n\n// From messages/i18n.ts\nimport { Exit, Match, pipe, SchemaIssue } from \"effect\";\nimport * as O from \"effect/Option\";\nimport * as S from \"effect/Schema\";\n```\n\n#### Effect Usage Patterns:\n\n1. **Function Pipeline** (`F.dual`, `pipe`):\n```typescript\nexport const dotGet: { ... } = F.dual(2, <S extends object>(self: S, path: PathInput): unknown => {\n  const lookup = lookupAtPath(self, path);\n  return lookup.found ? lookup.value : undefined;\n}) as { ... };\n```\n\n2. **Option-based Returns**:\n```typescript\nexport const dotGetOption: { ... } = F.dual(2, <S extends object>(self: S, path: PathInput): O.Option<unknown> => {\n  const lookup = lookupAtPath(self, path);\n  return lookup.found ? O.some(lookup.value) : O.none();\n}) as { ... };\n```\n\n3. **Match Expressions**:\n```typescript\nconst matchInvalidIssue = Match.type<SchemaIssue.InvalidType[\"ast\"]>().pipe(\n  Match.tags({\n    String: () => t(\"string.mismatch\"),\n    Objects: () => t(\"struct.mismatch\"),\n  }),\n  Match.orElse(() => t(\"default.mismatch\"))\n);\n```\n\n4. **Effect-based Thunks**:\n```typescript\nexport const thunkEffect = <A, E, R>(effect: Effect.Effect<A, E, R>): LazyArg<Effect.Effect<A, E, R>> => \n  thunk(effect);\n\nexport const thunkEffectVoid = thunkEffect(Effect.void);\nexport const thunkEffectSucceed = <A>(a: A): LazyArg<Effect.Effect<unknown, never, A>> =>\n  thunkEffect(Effect.succeed(a));\n```\n\n5. **Schema Integration with Exit**:\n```typescript\nS.decodeUnknownExit(schema)(input, { errors: \"all\" }).pipe(\n  Exit.mapError((err) => SchemaIssue.makeFormatterStandardSchemaV1(options)(err.issue).issues)\n)\n```\n\n6. **Array and Record Operations**:\n```typescript\nconst result = A.filter(literals, isExcluded);\nconst entries = F.pipe(\n  segments,\n  A.map((segment) => { ... }),\n  A.reduce({} as EnumType<L>, (acc, literal) => ({ ...acc, ... }))\n);\nconst record = R.fromEntries(entries);\n```\n\n7. **Identity System with Effect Collections**:\n```typescript\nconst registry = MutableHashSet.empty<string>();\nconst keySet: HashSet.HashSet<SchemaAST.LiteralValue> = HashSet.fromIterable(subset);\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. CURRENT ERROR CHANNEL PATTERNS\n\n#### Error Flow Architecture:\n\n1. **Synchronous Schema Validation**:\n   - `S.decodeUnknownSync()` - throws synchronously on validation failure\n   - `S.decodeUnknownExit()` - returns `Exit<Type, ParseError>` for functional error handling\n\n2. **Effect-based Error Handling**:\n   - Uses `Exit<A, E>` type for error channels\n   - `Exit.mapError()` for error transformation\n   - Tagged error classes extend `S.TaggedErrorClass`\n\n3. **Schema Issue Formatting Pipeline**:\n```typescript\n// Three-layer error processing\nExit.mapError((err) => \n  SchemaIssue.makeFormatterStandardSchemaV1(options)(err.issue).issues\n)\n// Produces:\n// { path: string[], message: string }[]\n```\n\n4. **Custom Issue Hooks**:\n   - `leafHook`: Formats leaf-level issues (missing key, wrong type)\n   - `checkHook`: Formats custom validation errors\n   - Both use i18n (`t()` function) for messages\n\n5. **Error Annotation System**:\n```typescript\n// Errors annotated with identity metadata\nexport class ErrorName extends S.TaggedErrorClass<ErrorName>($I`ErrorName`)(\n  \"ErrorName\",\n  { /* fields */ },\n  $I.annote(\"ErrorName\", {\n    title: \"User-facing title\",\n    description: \"Detailed description\"\n  })\n) {}\n```\n\n#### Message Handling:\n\n```typescript\n// i18n translations for schema issues\nexport const leafHook = Match.type<SchemaIssue.Leaf>().pipe(\n  Match.tagsExhaustive({\n    InvalidType: (issue) => matchInvalidIssue(issue.ast),\n    InvalidValue: () => t(\"default.invalidValue\"),\n    MissingKey: () => t(\"struct.missingKey\"),\n    UnexpectedKey: () => t(\"struct.unexpectedKey\"),\n    Forbidden: () => t(\"default.forbidden\"),\n    OneOf: () => t(\"default.oneOf\"),\n  })\n);\n```\n\n#### Identity System Error Handling:\n\n```typescript\n// Segment validation using schema filters\nconst SegmentCheck = S.makeFilterGroup([\n  S.makeFilter((segment: string) => Str.isNonEmpty(segment), {\n    identifier: \"@beep/identity/check/non-empty-segment\",\n    message: \"Identity segments cannot be empty.\",\n  }),\n  S.makeFilter((segment: string) => !F.pipe(segment, Str.startsWith(\"/\")), {\n    identifier: \"@beep/identity/check/no-leading-slash\",\n    message: 'Identity segments cannot start with \"/\".',\n  }),\n  // ... more filters\n]);\n\n// Validation throws via decoder\nconst validateSegment = <const Segment extends TString.NonEmpty>(segment: Segment): Segment => {\n  decodeSegment(segment);  // throws if invalid\n  return segment;\n};\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. KEY ARCHITECTURAL PATTERNS\n\n#### Dual API Pattern (from Struct.ts):\n```typescript\n// Supports both data-first and data-last usage\nexport const dotGet: {\n  <const P extends string>(path: P): <S extends object>(self: ...) => ...;  // curried\n  <S extends object, const P extends StructPath<S>>(self: S, path: P): ...;  // direct\n} = F.dual(2, (self: S, path: PathInput): unknown => { ... });\n```\n\n#### Type-Level Path Resolution:\n- Recursive depth-bounded type traversal (max depth 10)\n- Rejects open index-signature records\n- Stops at arrays, functions, and primitive leaves\n- Includes `undefined` in results when crossing optional properties\n\n#### Identity Composer Pattern:\n- Builder pattern for hierarchical identity strings\n- Template tag support with validation\n- Registry tracking for all created identities\n- Annotation system for schema metadata\n\n#### Thunk Factory Pattern:\n```typescript\nexport const thunk = <A>(value: A): LazyArg<A> => () => value;\nexport const thunkNull = thunk(null);\nexport const thunkUndefined = thunk(undefined);\n// ... pre-made thunks for common values\n```\n\n---\n\n### 7. TESTING PATTERNS\n\n#### Runtime Tests (Vitest):\n```typescript\n// From structGet.test.ts - using @effect/vitest\nimport { describe, expect, expectTypeOf, it } from \"vitest\";\n\nit(\"supports data-first and data-last calls\", () => {\n  const source = { attributes: { name: \"beep\" }, kind: \"example\" } as const;\n  const dataFirst = dotGet(source, \"attributes.name\");\n  const dataLast = pipe(source, dotGet(\"attributes.name\"));\n  expect(dataFirst).toBe(\"beep\");\n  expectTypeOf(dataFirst).toEqualTypeOf<\"beep\">();\n});\n```\n\n#### Type-Level Tests (tstyche):\n```typescript\n// From structGet.tst.ts - using tstyche\nimport { describe, expect, it } from \"tstyche\";\n\nit(\"resolves nested path value types\", () => {\n  const source = { attributes: { name: \"beep\" as const } } as const;\n  expect(dotGet(source, \"attributes.name\")).type.toBe<\"beep\">();\n  expect(dotGet(source, [\"attributes\", \"name\"] as const)).type.toBe<\"beep\">();\n});\n\nit(\"rejects invalid or open-record paths\", () => {\n  const source = { attributes: { name: \"beep\" } } as const;\n  const notAStruct = {} as Record<string, unknown>;\n  \n  // @ts-expect-error not assignable to parameter of type\n  dotGet(source, \"attributes.missing\");\n  \n  // @ts-expect-error not assignable to parameter of type\n  dotGet(notAStruct, \"attributes.name\");\n});\n```\n\n#### Error Testing:\n```typescript\n// From Identity.test.ts\nit(\"throws schema validation messages for invalid values\", () => {\n  const $I = make(\"beep\").$BeepId;\n  expect(() => ($I.make as (segment: string) => unknown)(\"/bad\")).toThrowError(\n    'Identity segments cannot start with \"/\".'\n  );\n});\n\nit(\"rejects interpolations in identity template tags\", () => {\n  const $I = make(\"beep\").$BeepId.create(\"module\");\n  expect(\n    () => ($I as unknown as (s: TemplateStringsArray, ...v: ReadonlyArray<unknown>) => unknown)`My${\"Svc\"}`\n  ).toThrowError(\"Identity template tags do not allow interpolations.\");\n});\n```\n\n---\n\n### 8. CONFIGURATION SUMMARY\n\n**package.json**:\n- Uses `effect` catalog dependency\n- Exports via `.ts` files in src (TypeScript-first)\n- Babel transpilation with `annotate-pure-calls` plugin\n- Biome for linting, tstyche for type testing\n- `@effect/vitest` for runtime testing\n\n**tsconfig.json**:\n- Extends `../../../tsconfig.base.json`\n- References `../types/tsconfig.json`\n- Output to `dist/` directory\n\n**vitest.config.ts**:\n- Merges shared vitest config\n- Allows package-specific test overrides\n\n---\n\n### 9. UNIQUE PATTERNS AND CONVENTIONS\n\n1. **\"bench\" comments**: All source files end with `// bench` comment (likely for benchmarking)\n\n2. **Since 0.0.0**: All exports use JSDoc `@since 0.0.0` tags\n\n3. **Identity-driven Architecture**: \n   - All schemas and errors use identity system (`$I`, `$SchemaId`)\n   - Supports composition like `$SchemaId.create(\"module\").annote(\"EntityName\")`\n\n4. **Structural Validation**:\n   - Rejects `Record<string, any>` patterns\n   - Requires fixed, known keys at type level\n\n5. **Dual APIs**:\n   - `F.dual()` for flexible data-first/data-last calling conventions\n\n6. **Type-safe Unsafe Escape**:\n   - `TUnsafe.Any` - intentionally painful `any` type for accountability\n\n---\n\nThis codebase demonstrates a production-grade Effect-based TypeScript library with:\n- Strict type safety with recursive type traversal\n- Schema-driven validation and error handling\n- Identity-based metadata and annotations\n- Comprehensive test coverage (runtime + type-level)\n- Clean functional patterns using Effect utilities"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: acc9f453d97af5035 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 91334\ntool_uses: 33\nduration_ms: 83691</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ed826b28-f569-4d3f-95d3-b6409c9f2336","uuid":"e670f808-6c97-4783-b5ff-21b2c9005082","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the codebase at /home/elpresidank/.cache/beep-effect3/agent-eval/worktrees/package_lib_01__minimal__claude__1__1772060740989-67420/packages/common/utils/src and provide a thorough overview of:\n1. All files present and their contents\n2. Any existing error classes or error handling patterns\n3. How Schema is used\n4. How Effect is used\n5. Current error channel patterns\n\nAlso look at:\n- packages/common/utils/ (package.json, tsconfig, etc.)\n- Any sibling packages in packages/common/ for patterns to follow\n\nBe very thorough - show me the actual file contents.","agentId":"acc9f453d97af5035","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have a comprehensive view of the codebase. Let me create a thorough summary document.\n\n## Comprehensive Codebase Overview: @beep/utils and Common Packages\n\n### 1. FILES PRESENT AND CONTENTS\n\n#### `/packages/common/utils/` Structure:\n```\nutils/\n├── src/\n│   ├── index.ts          - Main export file\n│   ├── Struct.ts         - Struct path utilities\n│   └── thunk.ts          - Thunk/lazy value utilities\n├── test/\n│   └── structGet.test.ts  - Runtime tests for struct utilities\n├── dtslint/\n│   └── structGet.tst.ts   - Type-level tests using tstyche\n├── package.json          - Workspace package definition\n├── tsconfig.json         - TypeScript configuration\n├── vitest.config.ts      - Test configuration\n├── docgen.json           - Documentation generation config\n└── README.md             - Package documentation\n```\n\n#### `/packages/common/` Sibling Packages:\n- **messages** - i18n and schema issue formatting\n- **identity** - ID system with identity composers and schema annotations\n- **schema** - Schema utilities (LiteralKit, ArrayOf)\n- **data** - MIME types, timezones, currencies\n- **ontology** - (minimal, version export only)\n- **types** - Type utilities (TString.NonEmpty, TUnsafe.Any)\n\n---\n\n### 2. ERROR CLASSES AND ERROR HANDLING PATTERNS\n\n#### Error Classes Found:\n\n**In @beep/identity/Id.ts:**\n```typescript\nexport class IdentityInterpolationError extends S.TaggedErrorClass<IdentityInterpolationError>(\n  \"@beep/identity/errors/IdentityInterpolationError\"\n)(\"IdentityInterpolationError\", {}, { ... }) {}\n\nexport class IdentitySegmentCountError extends S.TaggedErrorClass<IdentitySegmentCountError>(\n  \"@beep/identity/errors/IdentitySegmentCountError\"\n)(\"IdentitySegmentCountError\", {}, { ... }) {}\n```\n\n**In @beep/schema/LiteralKit.ts:**\n```typescript\nexport class LiteralNotInSetError extends S.TaggedErrorClass<LiteralNotInSetError>($I`LiteralNotInSetError`)(\n  \"LiteralNotInSetError\",\n  {\n    literals: S.Array(LiteralValueSchema),\n    input: S.Array(LiteralValueSchema),\n  },\n  $I.annote(\"LiteralNotInSetError\", {\n    title: \"Not In Literals Error\",\n    description: \"Error thrown when an input value is not found in the provided literals array.\",\n  })\n) {}\n```\n\n#### Error Handling Patterns:\n\n1. **Schema-based Error Classes**: All errors extend `S.TaggedErrorClass` from Effect/Schema\n   - Provides structured error typing\n   - Integrates with schema serialization\n   - Uses identity system for error identification\n\n2. **Error Channel Pattern** (via Effect):\n   - Errors wrapped in schema validation context\n   - Uses `S.decodeUnknownSync()` and related decode functions\n   - Exceptions thrown synchronously for validation failures\n\n3. **Schema Validation Errors**:\n   - Schema issues use `SchemaIssue` types from Effect\n   - Formatted via `SchemaIssue.makeFormatterStandardSchemaV1(options)(err.issue)`\n   - Custom hooks for leaf and check issues via i18n\n\n---\n\n### 3. HOW SCHEMA IS USED\n\n#### Schema Integration Pattern:\n\n```typescript\n// From @beep/identity/Id.ts\nconst SegmentSchema = S.String.check(SegmentCheck);\nconst ModuleSegmentSchema = SegmentSchema.check(ModuleSegmentCheck);\nconst BaseSegmentSchema = S.String.check(...);\n\n// Decode utilities created from schemas\nconst decodeString = S.decodeUnknownSync(S.String);\nconst decodeSegment = S.decodeUnknownSync(SegmentSchema);\nconst decodeModuleSegment = S.decodeUnknownSync(ModuleSegmentSchema);\nconst decodeBaseSegment = S.decodeUnknownSync(BaseSegmentSchema);\n```\n\n#### Schema Annotations with Identity:\n\n```typescript\n// From @beep/schema/ArrayOf.ts\nconst $I = $SchemaId.create(\"ArrayOf\");\nexport const ArrayOfStrings = S.Array(S.String).annotate(\n  $I.annote(\"ArrayOfStrings\", {\n    description: \"An array of strings\",\n  })\n);\n```\n\n#### Error Schema Definition:\n\n```typescript\n// From @beep/schema/LiteralKit.ts\nconst LiteralValueSchema = S.Union([S.String, S.BigInt, S.Boolean, S.Number]);\n\nexport class LiteralNotInSetError extends S.TaggedErrorClass<LiteralNotInSetError>($I`LiteralNotInSetError`)(\n  \"LiteralNotInSetError\",\n  {\n    literals: S.Array(LiteralValueSchema),\n    input: S.Array(LiteralValueSchema),\n  },\n  // ... annotations\n) {}\n```\n\n#### Schema Usage in Messages:\n\n```typescript\n// From @beep/messages/i18n.ts\nexport function getLogIssues(options?: GetLogIssuesOptions) {\n  return <S extends S.Codec<unknown, unknown>>(schema: S, input: unknown) => {\n    S.decodeUnknownExit(schema)(input, { errors: \"all\" }).pipe(\n      Exit.mapError((err) => SchemaIssue.makeFormatterStandardSchemaV1(options)(err.issue).issues)\n    )\n  };\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. HOW EFFECT IS USED\n\n#### Effect Imports and Patterns:\n\n**Core Effect Utilities:**\n```typescript\n// From Struct.ts\nimport { Function as F, String as Str } from \"effect\";\nimport * as O from \"effect/Option\";\nimport * as P from \"effect/Predicate\";\n\n// From thunk.ts\nimport { Effect } from \"effect\";\nimport * as A from \"effect/Array\";\nimport * as R from \"effect/Record\";\n\n// From messages/i18n.ts\nimport { Exit, Match, pipe, SchemaIssue } from \"effect\";\nimport * as O from \"effect/Option\";\nimport * as S from \"effect/Schema\";\n```\n\n#### Effect Usage Patterns:\n\n1. **Function Pipeline** (`F.dual`, `pipe`):\n```typescript\nexport const dotGet: { ... } = F.dual(2, <S extends object>(self: S, path: PathInput): unknown => {\n  const lookup = lookupAtPath(self, path);\n  return lookup.found ? lookup.value : undefined;\n}) as { ... };\n```\n\n2. **Option-based Returns**:\n```typescript\nexport const dotGetOption: { ... } = F.dual(2, <S extends object>(self: S, path: PathInput): O.Option<unknown> => {\n  const lookup = lookupAtPath(self, path);\n  return lookup.found ? O.some(lookup.value) : O.none();\n}) as { ... };\n```\n\n3. **Match Expressions**:\n```typescript\nconst matchInvalidIssue = Match.type<SchemaIssue.InvalidType[\"ast\"]>().pipe(\n  Match.tags({\n    String: () => t(\"string.mismatch\"),\n    Objects: () => t(\"struct.mismatch\"),\n  }),\n  Match.orElse(() => t(\"default.mismatch\"))\n);\n```\n\n4. **Effect-based Thunks**:\n```typescript\nexport const thunkEffect = <A, E, R>(effect: Effect.Effect<A, E, R>): LazyArg<Effect.Effect<A, E, R>> => \n  thunk(effect);\n\nexport const thunkEffectVoid = thunkEffect(Effect.void);\nexport const thunkEffectSucceed = <A>(a: A): LazyArg<Effect.Effect<unknown, never, A>> =>\n  thunkEffect(Effect.succeed(a));\n```\n\n5. **Schema Integration with Exit**:\n```typescript\nS.decodeUnknownExit(schema)(input, { errors: \"all\" }).pipe(\n  Exit.mapError((err) => SchemaIssue.makeFormatterStandardSchemaV1(options)(err.issue).issues)\n)\n```\n\n6. **Array and Record Operations**:\n```typescript\nconst result = A.filter(literals, isExcluded);\nconst entries = F.pipe(\n  segments,\n  A.map((segment) => { ... }),\n  A.reduce({} as EnumType<L>, (acc, literal) => ({ ...acc, ... }))\n);\nconst record = R.fromEntries(entries);\n```\n\n7. **Identity System with Effect Collections**:\n```typescript\nconst registry = MutableHashSet.empty<string>();\nconst keySet: HashSet.HashSet<SchemaAST.LiteralValue> = HashSet.fromIterable(subset);\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. CURRENT ERROR CHANNEL PATTERNS\n\n#### Error Flow Architecture:\n\n1. **Synchronous Schema Validation**:\n   - `S.decodeUnknownSync()` - throws synchronously on validation failure\n   - `S.decodeUnknownExit()` - returns `Exit<Type, ParseError>` for functional error handling\n\n2. **Effect-based Error Handling**:\n   - Uses `Exit<A, E>` type for error channels\n   - `Exit.mapError()` for error transformation\n   - Tagged error classes extend `S.TaggedErrorClass`\n\n3. **Schema Issue Formatting Pipeline**:\n```typescript\n// Three-layer error processing\nExit.mapError((err) => \n  SchemaIssue.makeFormatterStandardSchemaV1(options)(err.issue).issues\n)\n// Produces:\n// { path: string[], message: string }[]\n```\n\n4. **Custom Issue Hooks**:\n   - `leafHook`: Formats leaf-level issues (missing key, wrong type)\n   - `checkHook`: Formats custom validation errors\n   - Both use i18n (`t()` function) for messages\n\n5. **Error Annotation System**:\n```typescript\n// Errors annotated with identity metadata\nexport class ErrorName extends S.TaggedErrorClass<ErrorName>($I`ErrorName`)(\n  \"ErrorName\",\n  { /* fields */ },\n  $I.annote(\"ErrorName\", {\n    title: \"User-facing title\",\n    description: \"Detailed description\"\n  })\n) {}\n```\n\n#### Message Handling:\n\n```typescript\n// i18n translations for schema issues\nexport const leafHook = Match.type<SchemaIssue.Leaf>().pipe(\n  Match.tagsExhaustive({\n    InvalidType: (issue) => matchInvalidIssue(issue.ast),\n    InvalidValue: () => t(\"default.invalidValue\"),\n    MissingKey: () => t(\"struct.missingKey\"),\n    UnexpectedKey: () => t(\"struct.unexpectedKey\"),\n    Forbidden: () => t(\"default.forbidden\"),\n    OneOf: () => t(\"default.oneOf\"),\n  })\n);\n```\n\n#### Identity System Error Handling:\n\n```typescript\n// Segment validation using schema filters\nconst SegmentCheck = S.makeFilterGroup([\n  S.makeFilter((segment: string) => Str.isNonEmpty(segment), {\n    identifier: \"@beep/identity/check/non-empty-segment\",\n    message: \"Identity segments cannot be empty.\",\n  }),\n  S.makeFilter((segment: string) => !F.pipe(segment, Str.startsWith(\"/\")), {\n    identifier: \"@beep/identity/check/no-leading-slash\",\n    message: 'Identity segments cannot start with \"/\".',\n  }),\n  // ... more filters\n]);\n\n// Validation throws via decoder\nconst validateSegment = <const Segment extends TString.NonEmpty>(segment: Segment): Segment => {\n  decodeSegment(segment);  // throws if invalid\n  return segment;\n};\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. KEY ARCHITECTURAL PATTERNS\n\n#### Dual API Pattern (from Struct.ts):\n```typescript\n// Supports both data-first and data-last usage\nexport const dotGet: {\n  <const P extends string>(path: P): <S extends object>(self: ...) => ...;  // curried\n  <S extends object, const P extends StructPath<S>>(self: S, path: P): ...;  // direct\n} = F.dual(2, (self: S, path: PathInput): unknown => { ... });\n```\n\n#### Type-Level Path Resolution:\n- Recursive depth-bounded type traversal (max depth 10)\n- Rejects open index-signature records\n- Stops at arrays, functions, and primitive leaves\n- Includes `undefined` in results when crossing optional properties\n\n#### Identity Composer Pattern:\n- Builder pattern for hierarchical identity strings\n- Template tag support with validation\n- Registry tracking for all created identities\n- Annotation system for schema metadata\n\n#### Thunk Factory Pattern:\n```typescript\nexport const thunk = <A>(value: A): LazyArg<A> => () => value;\nexport const thunkNull = thunk(null);\nexport const thunkUndefined = thunk(undefined);\n// ... pre-made thunks for common values\n```\n\n---\n\n### 7. TESTING PATTERNS\n\n#### Runtime Tests (Vitest):\n```typescript\n// From structGet.test.ts - using @effect/vitest\nimport { describe, expect, expectTypeOf, it } from \"vitest\";\n\nit(\"supports data-first and data-last calls\", () => {\n  const source = { attributes: { name: \"beep\" }, kind: \"example\" } as const;\n  const dataFirst = dotGet(source, \"attributes.name\");\n  const dataLast = pipe(source, dotGet(\"attributes.name\"));\n  expect(dataFirst).toBe(\"beep\");\n  expectTypeOf(dataFirst).toEqualTypeOf<\"beep\">();\n});\n```\n\n#### Type-Level Tests (tstyche):\n```typescript\n// From structGet.tst.ts - using tstyche\nimport { describe, expect, it } from \"tstyche\";\n\nit(\"resolves nested path value types\", () => {\n  const source = { attributes: { name: \"beep\" as const } } as const;\n  expect(dotGet(source, \"attributes.name\")).type.toBe<\"beep\">();\n  expect(dotGet(source, [\"attributes\", \"name\"] as const)).type.toBe<\"beep\">();\n});\n\nit(\"rejects invalid or open-record paths\", () => {\n  const source = { attributes: { name: \"beep\" } } as const;\n  const notAStruct = {} as Record<string, unknown>;\n  \n  // @ts-expect-error not assignable to parameter of type\n  dotGet(source, \"attributes.missing\");\n  \n  // @ts-expect-error not assignable to parameter of type\n  dotGet(notAStruct, \"attributes.name\");\n});\n```\n\n#### Error Testing:\n```typescript\n// From Identity.test.ts\nit(\"throws schema validation messages for invalid values\", () => {\n  const $I = make(\"beep\").$BeepId;\n  expect(() => ($I.make as (segment: string) => unknown)(\"/bad\")).toThrowError(\n    'Identity segments cannot start with \"/\".'\n  );\n});\n\nit(\"rejects interpolations in identity template tags\", () => {\n  const $I = make(\"beep\").$BeepId.create(\"module\");\n  expect(\n    () => ($I as unknown as (s: TemplateStringsArray, ...v: ReadonlyArray<unknown>) => unknown)`My${\"Svc\"}`\n  ).toThrowError(\"Identity template tags do not allow interpolations.\");\n});\n```\n\n---\n\n### 8. CONFIGURATION SUMMARY\n\n**package.json**:\n- Uses `effect` catalog dependency\n- Exports via `.ts` files in src (TypeScript-first)\n- Babel transpilation with `annotate-pure-calls` plugin\n- Biome for linting, tstyche for type testing\n- `@effect/vitest` for runtime testing\n\n**tsconfig.json**:\n- Extends `../../../tsconfig.base.json`\n- References `../types/tsconfig.json`\n- Output to `dist/` directory\n\n**vitest.config.ts**:\n- Merges shared vitest config\n- Allows package-specific test overrides\n\n---\n\n### 9. UNIQUE PATTERNS AND CONVENTIONS\n\n1. **\"bench\" comments**: All source files end with `// bench` comment (likely for benchmarking)\n\n2. **Since 0.0.0**: All exports use JSDoc `@since 0.0.0` tags\n\n3. **Identity-driven Architecture**: \n   - All schemas and errors use identity system (`$I`, `$SchemaId`)\n   - Supports composition like `$SchemaId.create(\"module\").annote(\"EntityName\")`\n\n4. **Structural Validation**:\n   - Rejects `Record<string, any>` patterns\n   - Requires fixed, known keys at type level\n\n5. **Dual APIs**:\n   - `F.dual()` for flexible data-first/data-last calling conventions\n\n6. **Type-safe Unsafe Escape**:\n   - `TUnsafe.Any` - intentionally painful `any` type for accountability\n\n---\n\nThis codebase demonstrates a production-grade Effect-based TypeScript library with:\n- Strict type safety with recursive type traversal\n- Schema-driven validation and error handling\n- Identity-based metadata and annotations\n- Comprehensive test coverage (runtime + type-level)\n- Clean functional patterns using Effect utilities"}],"totalDurationMs":83691,"totalTokens":91334,"totalToolUseCount":33,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2142,"cache_read_input_tokens":84859,"output_tokens":4333,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2142,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
